### One-command install (works anywhere NullClaw runs â€” $5 RISC-V boards, Raspberry Pi, Docker, Nix, native Zig binary)

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/profbernardoj/null-everclaw/main/setup.sh | bash
```

Then:

```bash
nullclaw onboard          # only first time (or --interactive)
nullclaw service install  # optional: systemd / launchd / OpenRC
nullclaw daemon           # or nullclaw gateway / nullclaw agent
```

Your NullClaw instantly switches to **decentralized Morpheus inference** (GLM-5 heavy default, GLM-4.7-flash fast, Kimi K2.5, Qwen3-235b, etc.) via the local OpenAI-compatible proxy on `http://127.0.0.1:8083/v1`.

No Zig rebuild. No vtable changes. No API bills. Stake MOR once â†’ unlimited use forever. NullClawâ€™s 678 KB static binary, <2 ms startup, ~1 MB RAM, and full autonomy stay 100% untouched.

