### What setup.sh does automatically

1. Clones & installs the battle-tested EverClaw proxy + guardian (Node.js sidecar, ~80 MB total â€” still tiny next to NullClaw)
2. Starts proxy on boot (systemd user service / launchd / Nix-aware)
3. Runs `nullclaw onboard` if needed
4. Merges this into `~/.nullclaw/config.json` (backs up original):

```json
{
  "default_provider": "morpheus",
  "models": {
    "providers": {
      "morpheus": {
        "api_base": "http://127.0.0.1:8083/v1",
        "api_key": "sk-morpheus"
      }
    }
  },
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "glm-5"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

(You can still use all 22+ original providers â€” just switch `default_provider` or per-agent.)

5. Adds the `enable-morpheus` skill to `~/.nullclaw/workspace/skills/` for runtime control

### Staking (unlimited use â€” same as all EverClaw forks)

```bash
cd ~/.everclaw
node scripts/everclaw-wallet.mjs setup
node scripts/everclaw-wallet.mjs stake   # stake MOR, never spend it
```

### Test it

```bash
